<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>If you build a \Zend\Log\Logger that uses a Zend\Log\Writer\Stream to write to a file and register it as the logger in \Zend\Log\Logger::registerErrorHandler you end having a bad error_handler since doWrite in Zend\Log\Writer\Stream uses Zend\StfdLib\ErrorHandler to catch error generated by fwrite. As Zend\StfdLib\ErrorHandler also registers an error_handler you end up trying to call restore_error_handler() from an error_handler function, which according to <a href="http://www.php.net/manual/en/function.restore-error-handler.php">http://php.net/manual/en/â€¦</a> is impossible.</p>

<p>I will make a pull request on github including a test case and a possible fix.</p>

